WESTERN POWER, LIGHT & TELEPHONE COMPANY et al. v. CITY OF WOODWARD, OKLAHOMA et al. No. 443. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 1, 1931. Howard W. Patton, of Woodward, Okl., W. R. Bleakmore and John Barry, both of Oklahoma City, OH., for appellants. J. B. Dudley, of OHahoma City, Okl., Y. Q. Caldwell, Jr., of Paris, Tenn., and C. W. Herod, of Woodward, OH., for appellees.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and Mc-DERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed June 1,1931, per stipulation.
